<% content_for :title, "API docs — Printwright" %>
<div class="container">
  <h1>API docs</h1>
  <p class="t-small muted">Everything below is either rendered live from <%= link_to "/openapi.json", "/openapi.json" %>
    or grep-verified against this running app — nothing here can quietly drift from the real
    contract. Machine-readable summary: <%= link_to "/llms.txt", "/llms.txt" %>.</p>

  <h2>Quickstart</h2>
  <p class="t-small">A purchase is one HTTP negotiation: probe, get a <code>402</code>, sign a
    Hedera transaction client-side, retry, get the file. Signing can't be done in curl — that
    step needs a Hedera key, so the one-command version is
    <code>node scripts/buy.mjs --query "..." --max-price 300</code> (<code>--help</code> lists
    the flags). What follows is the real trace, endpoint and headers included.</p>
  <p class="t-small">No funded account yet? Add <code>--dry-run</code> to stop at the
    <code>402</code> and print the payment requirements — the whole negotiation, no keys and no
    money. That is the fastest way to see the contract before you fund anything.</p>
  <pre class="mono t-small" style="overflow-x:auto"># 1. Probe: call the paid endpoint with no payment attached
curl -i "http://localhost:3000/api/v1/models/5/download?license=personal"
#   HTTP/1.1 402 Payment Required
#   payment-required: eyJ4NDAyVmVyc2lvbiI6Mi...        (base64 of the JSON body below)
#   {"x402Version":2,"error":"payment required","resource":{"url":"...","description":"..."},
#    "accepts":[
#      {"scheme":"exact","network":"hedera:testnet","payTo":"0.0.9604186","amount":"900000",
#       "asset":"0.0.429274","extra":{"feePayer":"0.0.7162784"},"maxTimeoutSeconds":180},
#      {"scheme":"exact","network":"hedera:testnet","payTo":"0.0.9604186","amount":"1358695652",
#       "asset":"0.0.0","extra":{"feePayer":"0.0.7162784"},"maxTimeoutSeconds":180}]}

# 2. Pick one `accepts` entry (asset 0.0.0 = HBAR tinybars, 0.0.429274 = testnet USDC).
#    Sign a Hedera TransferTransaction with transactionId.accountId = extra.feePayer
#    (buyer signature only — the fee payer sponsors network fees and submits).
#    This step is not curl-able; scripts/buy.mjs does it for you.

# 3. Retry the identical URL with the base64 PaymentPayload in PAYMENT-SIGNATURE:
curl -i "http://localhost:3000/api/v1/models/5/download?license=personal" \
  -H "PAYMENT-SIGNATURE: &lt;base64 PaymentPayload&gt;"
#   HTTP/1.1 200 OK
#   payment-response: eyJ0cmFuc2FjdGlvbiI6Ii4uLiJ9    (base64 settlement receipt)
#   { "files": [...], "license": {"cert_id": "pw-000036", "serial": 3, "kind": "personal"},
#     "certificate": {...}, "transaction_id": "...", "hashscan_url": "https://hashscan.io/..." }</pre>

  <h2>JavaScript client</h2>
  <p class="t-small"><code class="mono">@printwright/client</code> wraps catalog reads, the
    x402 Hedera signature, optional first-use USDC association, and HCS certificate comparison.
    From this repository install it with <code class="mono">npm install ./client</code>; the
    registry command after release is <code class="mono">npm install @printwright/client</code>.
    This five-line read-only quickstart needs no funded account:</p>
  <pre class="mono t-small" style="overflow-x:auto">import { PrintwrightClient } from "@printwright/client";
const printwright = new PrintwrightClient({ baseUrl: "http://localhost:3000" });
const { models } = await printwright.search({ query: "cable clip", maxPriceCents: 300 });
const model = await printwright.get(models[0].id);
console.log(model.title, model.license_offers);</pre>
  <p class="t-small">Catalog results also expose stable <code class="mono">category</code> and
    <code class="mono">collections</code> keys. Filter with, for example,
    <code class="mono">category=workshop-tools</code> or
    <code class="mono">collection=under-an-hour</code>; the allowed values are enumerated in the
    OpenAPI table below.</p>
  <p class="t-small">Add <code class="mono">accountId</code> and
    <code class="mono">privateKey</code> to the constructor to call
    <code class="mono">buy()</code>. The key remains local. Use <code class="mono">quote()</code>
    for an unsigned approval/dry-run view and <code class="mono">verify(certId)</code> to compare
    the marketplace certificate with its public mirror-node message.</p>

  <h3>Try the whole flow free</h3>
  <p class="t-small">Sandbox mode performs the same 402 → mock verify → mock settle → certificate
    sequence with no Hedera account, key, association, or funds. It returns only a text receipt,
    never paid geometry. Every identifier, response, verify page, and topic message says
    <strong>SANDBOX</strong>; none is a payment or license:</p>
  <pre class="mono t-small" style="overflow-x:auto">import { PrintwrightClient } from "@printwright/client";
const sandbox = new PrintwrightClient({ baseUrl: "http://localhost:3000", sandbox: true });
const { models } = await sandbox.search({ query: "cable clip" });
const receipt = await sandbox.buy({ modelId: models[0].id, license: "personal" });
console.log(receipt.warning, await sandbox.verify(receipt.license.cert_id));</pre>
  <p class="t-small">The CLI equivalent is
    <code class="mono">node scripts/buy.mjs --query "cable clip" --sandbox</code>. Raw HTTP
    clients send <code class="mono">X-Sandbox: true</code> on both the initial download request
    and its <code class="mono">PAYMENT-SIGNATURE</code> retry.</p>

  <h2>Endpoint reference</h2>
  <p class="t-small muted">Generated from <%= link_to "/openapi.json", "/openapi.json" %> at request
    time — the tables below are that file, not a hand-kept copy.</p>

  <% @openapi["paths"].each do |path, methods| %>
    <% methods.each do |verb, op| %>
      <h3><code class="mono"><%= verb.upcase %> <%= @openapi.dig("servers", 0, "url") %><%= path %></code></h3>
      <p class="t-small"><%= op["summary"] %></p>
      <% if op["description"].present? %>
        <p class="t-small muted"><%= op["description"] %></p>
      <% end %>

      <% if op["parameters"].present? %>
        <div class="table-scroll">
          <table class="facts-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Param</th><th>In</th><th>Type</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <% op["parameters"].each do |param| %>
                <tr>
                  <td><code class="mono"><%= param["name"] %></code></td>
                  <td><%= param["in"] %></td>
                  <td><%= param.dig("schema", "type") %></td>
                  <td class="t-small muted"><%= param["description"] %></td>
                </tr>
              <% end %>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      <% end %>

      <div class="table-scroll">
        <table class="facts-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <% op["responses"].each do |code, resp| %>
              <% resp = openapi_deref(@openapi, resp) %>
              <tr>
                <td><%= code %></td>
                <td class="t-small">
                  <%= resp["description"] %>
                  <% if resp["headers"].present? %>
                    <br><span class="muted">headers: <%= resp["headers"].keys.join(", ") %></span>
                  <% end %>
                </td>
              </tr>
            <% end %>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>

  <h2>Error contract</h2>
  <div class="table-scroll">
    <table class="facts-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>error</th><th>Where</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>400</td><td><code class="mono">invalid_payload</code></td><td>download — PAYMENT-SIGNATURE not decodable</td></tr>
        <tr><td>402</td><td><code class="mono">payment required</code></td><td>download — no payment attached</td></tr>
        <tr><td>402</td><td><code class="mono">invalid_payment_requirements</code></td><td>download — attached payment matches no <code class="mono">accepts</code> entry</td></tr>
        <tr><td>404</td><td><code class="mono">not_found</code></td><td>any resource missing</td></tr>
        <tr><td>409</td><td><code class="mono">duplicate_payment</code> (+ <code class="mono">status</code>)</td><td>download — replayed payment (a replay of an already-delivered purchase instead returns the original delivery payload, not this error)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>410</td><td><code class="mono">sold_out</code></td><td>download — offer <code class="mono">max_units</code> exhausted (may include <code class="mono">transaction_id</code> when it sold out after payment)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>410</td><td><code class="mono">grant_expired</code></td><td>files — download grant no longer usable</td></tr>
        <tr><td>429</td><td><code class="mono">rate_limited</code> (+ <code class="mono">retry_after: 60</code>)</td><td>all API endpoints; also sets <code class="mono">Retry-After: 60</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td>503</td><td><code class="mono">facilitator_unavailable</code> (+ <code class="mono">retry_after: 5</code>)</td><td>download — facilitator down / circuit breaker open</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p class="t-small">Per-endpoint rate limits, all on a 1-minute window (so a 429's
    <code class="mono">Retry-After</code> is always 60): <code class="mono">/models</code> and
    <code class="mono">/models/{id}</code> and <code class="mono">/certificates/{cert_id}</code>
    120/min, <code class="mono">/models/{id}/download</code> 30/min,
    <code class="mono">/files/{token}</code> 60/min.</p>

  <h2>MCP</h2>
  <p class="t-small">The MCP server exposes the same door to any MCP client (Claude Code, Claude
    Desktop, ...):</p>
  <pre class="mono t-small" style="overflow-x:auto">cd mcp && npm install && cd ..
claude mcp add printwright \
  --env PRINTWRIGHT_URL=http://localhost:3000 \
  --env BUYER_ACCOUNT_ID=0.0.xxxxxxx \
  --env BUYER_PRIVATE_KEY=0x... \
  --env MAX_SPEND_CENTS=500 \
  -- node mcp/server.mjs</pre>
  <p class="t-small">Four tools: <code class="mono">search_models</code>,
    <code class="mono">get_model</code>, <code class="mono">buy_license</code> (refuses without
    <code class="mono">confirm: true</code>, capped by <code class="mono">MAX_SPEND_CENTS</code>),
    and <code class="mono">verify_certificate</code> (reads the HCS message from the public
    mirror and diffs it against the marketplace copy).</p>

  <h2>Networks</h2>
  <p class="t-small">One switch, <code class="mono">HEDERA_NETWORK</code>, flips every
    network-dependent value below.</p>
  <div class="table-scroll">
    <table class="facts-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>testnet</th><th>mainnet</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><th scope="row">CAIP-2 network id</th><td><code class="mono">hedera:testnet</code></td><td><code class="mono">hedera:mainnet</code></td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">USDC token id</th><td><code class="mono">0.0.429274</code></td><td><code class="mono">0.0.456858</code></td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">USDC decimals</th><td>6</td><td>6</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">HBAR asset id</th><td colspan="2"><code class="mono">0.0.0</code> — always, on either network</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">Mirror node</th><td colspan="2"><code class="mono">https://&lt;network&gt;.mirrornode.hedera.com</code>, overridable with <code class="mono">MIRROR_NODE_URL</code></td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row">HashScan</th><td colspan="2"><code class="mono">https://hashscan.io/&lt;network&gt;</code></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>More</h2>
  <ul class="t-small">
    <li><%= link_to "/openapi.json", "/openapi.json" %> — the full machine-readable spec</li>
